=Description=

"In this project, I want to explore psychoterratic states and how they affect us in our daily lives.
Psychoterratic states are emotions that people feel in relation to the earth. The term was created
by Professor Glenn Albrecht of Murdoch University, who observed the need for a new
vocabulary to describe the emotions we feel as we witness the historical degradation of the
planet on a global scale. The term literally translates to earth psyche with “psycho” meaning
psyche, and “terratic” meaning earth. This will be the focus of my thesis project, 
'''looking at the emotional states we experience in the face of environmental disasters and how those emotions affect our responses'''."

